# 🔒 Security Policy

## Supported Versions

| Version | Supported |
|---|---|
| `1.x` (latest)  | ✅ Yes |
| `< 1.0`         | ❌ No  |

The CureCoders demo at https://orchids-curecoders.vercel.app/ always tracks
the latest `main` build. Older deployments are not patched.

---

## Reporting a Vulnerability

We take security seriously at **CureCoders — Pharmaceutical Intelligence
Platform**. If you discover a security vulnerability, please report it
**responsibly**.

### 🔒 How to Report

> ⚠️ **DO NOT open a public GitHub issue for security vulnerabilities.**

Please report via one of:

1. **Preferred:** Open a [private security advisory on GitHub](https://github.com/Samrudh2006/orchids-curecoders/security/advisories/new)
2. Contact the maintainer (**Samrudh**) directly through the contact details
   listed on the GitHub profile linked from this repository.

### What to Include

- **Description** of the vulnerability
- **Steps to reproduce** the issue
- **Impact assessment** — what could an attacker do?
- **Affected URLs / routes / endpoints**
- **Suggested fix** (if you have one)
- Any **proof-of-concept** code or screenshots (please redact PII)

### Response Timeline

| Action | Timeline |
|---|---|
| Acknowledgment | Within **48 hours** |
| Initial assessment | Within **5 business days** |
| Fix deployed (critical) | Within **14 business days** |
| Public disclosure | After fix is deployed and verified |

