## Security Measures in Place

### Application Layer
- ✅ **TanStack Start server functions** with strict input validation
- ✅ **Zod schemas** on every server-function input
- ✅ **Type-safe routing** via TanStack Router (no string-injection routes)
- ✅ **No client-side secrets** — all sensitive keys live in environment variables
- ✅ **Sandboxed file parsing** for uploaded documents (PDF / Word / Excel / PPT)

### AI & Agent Safety
- ✅ Each AI agent runs with a **system prompt forbidding medical advice**
- ✅ Agent outputs are **labeled as AI-generated** in the UI
- ✅ **Source citations required** for fact-style outputs
- ✅ Prompts are **stored server-side**, not exposed to the client
- ✅ Mock data clearly marked as **illustrative, not clinical evidence**

### Data Handling
- ✅ Demo mode does **not persist** user-uploaded documents
- ✅ No PII is collected, stored, or transmitted to third parties beyond
  the AI provider (when configured)
- ✅ No real patient data, EHR data, or confidential pharma data is shipped
  with the repository

### Infrastructure
- ✅ **HTTPS enforced** on all deployed routes (Vercel)
- ✅ Edge runtime (**Cloudflare Workers**) — no long-lived server processes
- ✅ Immutable asset caching with versioned URLs
- ✅ **Dependabot** alerts enabled for dependency vulnerabilities
- ✅ Secrets scoped to the deployment environment, not bundled

---

## Scope

The following are **in scope** for vulnerability reports:

- Authentication / authorization bypass (when auth is added)
- Server-function input validation bypass
- Server-side request forgery (SSRF) via mock API or upload handlers
- Cross-site scripting (XSS) — stored or reflected
- Cross-site request forgery (CSRF) on state-changing endpoints
- Sensitive data exposure (API keys, tokens, environment variables)
- Prompt injection that exfiltrates server-side prompts or secrets
- Path traversal or arbitrary file read via the upload pipeline
- Dependency vulnerabilities with a viable exploit path in this app

The following are **out of scope**:

- Social engineering of maintainers or users
- Denial of service (DoS) — Vercel / Cloudflare handle infrastructure DoS
- Issues requiring physical access to a user's device
- Issues in third-party services (FDA, USPTO, OpenAI, Vercel, Cloudflare,
  Supabase, etc.) — please report those upstream
- Self-XSS or issues requiring an attacker-controlled browser extension
- Best-practice findings without a demonstrable security impact
- Reports that "the AI said something wrong" — model output quality is a
  product issue, not a security issue (unless it leaks server-side data)

